        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="content-box highlight-box-alt">
              <h4>Consultation</h4>
              <p><ul><li>We take an hour or more to walk through your space, talk to you, and understand your needs. We charge $150 for the session, but if you proceed with an installation we credit that back towards the project.</li></ul></p>

              <h4>Solution Design</h4>
              <p><ul><li>We work with you to design a customized garden that will beautify your space and mesh with your lifestyle. Design budget is set in advance, based on the size and complexity of the project.</li></ul></p>

              <h4>Installation</h4>
              <p><ul><li>We transform your garden’s solutions-inspired design into reality. Installation can happen all at once, or gradually over time, depending on the scope of project and your budget.</li></ul></p>

              <!--h4>More Plants, Please!</h4>
              <p><ul><li>Whether it’s replacing cool season veggies with warm season, or upgrading your garden with additional beds/plantings, we’re happy to provide mid-season consultations and installations.</li></ul></p-->

              <h4>Seasonal Maintenance</h4>
              <p><ul><li>Your garden will be a living system that’ll require occasional maintenance to maximize its productivity and keep it looking awesome, especially while it is getting established. We can provide that maintenance.</li></ul></p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="content-box">
              <p>
                <a class="gallery-link" href="/#" data-index="0">
                  <img class="right-image services-image" src="<%=gallery[0].msrc%>" alt="<%= gallery[0].title %>"/>
                </a>
                If you have an outdoor space that needs some love -- be it a yard, a small urban plot, a rooftop, or an overgrown briar patch draped in popped birthday balloons and broken dreams -- we want to help you transform it into something more beautiful and enriching.
              </p>
              <p>
                Our projects work alongside nature, using nerdy yet attractive ecological designs that enrich life. You’ll become a plant-growing badass with the help of our hands-on training sessions, and most importantly, you’ll get the multitude of benefits that come alongside an attractive and practical outdoor space that enhances your local ecosystem and your culinary prowess.
              </p>
              <p>
                <a class="gallery-link" href="/#" data-index="1">
                  <img class="left-image services-image" src="<%=gallery[1].msrc%>" alt="<%= gallery[1].title %>"/>
                </a>
                Not everyone will be a good fit as our client, and we’re cool with that. Our goal is to start and maintain mutually beneficial relationships with folks who have an appreciation for our planet and a shared passion for quality food. Once we find clients that are a good match for Nightshade, we’ll work our asses off to deliver a high quality product/service and provide you with on-going support.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="content-box">
              <center>
                <a href="/gallery" class="btn btn-lg btn-action">Pictures Worth 1000 Words</a>
              </center>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Root element of PhotoSwipe. Must have class pswp. -->
        <div class="pswp" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">

            <!-- Background of PhotoSwipe.
                 It's a separate element as animating opacity is faster than rgba(). -->
            <div class="pswp__bg"></div>

            <!-- Slides wrapper with overflow:hidden. -->
            <div class="pswp__scroll-wrap">

                <!-- Container that holds slides.
                    PhotoSwipe keeps only 3 of them in the DOM to save memory.
                    Don't modify these 3 pswp__item elements, data is added later on. -->
                <div class="pswp__container">
                    <div class="pswp__item"></div>
                    <div class="pswp__item"></div>
                    <div class="pswp__item"></div>
                </div>

                <!-- Default (PhotoSwipeUI_Default) interface on top of sliding area. Can be changed. -->
                <div class="pswp__ui pswp__ui--hidden">

                    <div class="pswp__top-bar">

                        <!--  Controls are self-explanatory. Order can be changed. -->

                        <div class="pswp__counter"></div>

                        <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--close" title="Close (Esc)"></button>

                        <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--fs" title="Toggle fullscreen"></button>

                        <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--zoom" title="Zoom in/out"></button>

                        <!-- Preloader demo https://codepen.io/dimsemenov/pen/yyBWoR -->
                        <!-- element will get class pswp__preloader--active when preloader is running -->
                        <div class="pswp__preloader">
                            <div class="pswp__preloader__icn">
                              <div class="pswp__preloader__cut">
                                <div class="pswp__preloader__donut"></div>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--arrow--left" title="Previous (arrow left)">
                    </button>

                    <button class="pswp__button pswp__button--arrow--right" title="Next (arrow right)">
                    </button>

                    <div class="pswp__caption">
                        <div class="pswp__caption__center"></div>
                    </div>

                </div>

            </div>

        </div>
        <script src="./javascripts/photoswipe-init.js"></script>

      </div>
    </div>

  </body>
  <% include partials/footer %>
</html>
